               <birth notBefore="1828" notAfter="1829"/>
               <floruit notBefore="1840" notAfter="1860">He was 
                  the son of 
                  <persName ref="PRS8346sahlase">
                     <roleName type="title">nǝguś</roleName> Śahla Śǝllāse</persName> of <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName>
                  and his wife <persName ref="PRS11429Bazzabbe">Bazzabbǝš Daǧan</persName>.
                  He was the governor of <placeName ref="LOC4578Marhab">Marḥābete</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC5482Salale">Salāle</placeName> 
                  throughout <date>1840</date>s and <date>1850</date>s. <persName ref="PRS8602Sayfusa">Sayfu Śahla Śǝllāse</persName> was an ardent opponent  
                  to                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                      Tewodros II</persName> 
                  who offered a strong resistance for several days but was eventually defeated and had to flee. Some time later,
                  <persName ref="PRS8602Sayfusa">Sayfu Śahla Śǝllāse</persName> tried to regain control over  
                  <placeName ref="LOC4578Marhab">Marḥābete</placeName>, but was killed by <persName ref="PRS5902Kebrat">Kǝbrāt</persName>
                  at <placeName ref="LOC4811Midda">Middā</placeName>.</floruit>
               <death when="1860"/>
               
